gomodel:SYNGO_2859  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1: \"AMPA receptor CTs associate directly with AP2μ\"\nFig.3: \"Direct high-affinity binding of μ2-adaptin to the GluR2 CT\"\nFig.4: \"The GluR2-derived AP-2μ binding peptide targets a synaptotagmin 1 ΔC2B chimeric reporter protein for internalization\"\nFig.5: \"The Syt-1 AP-2 binding peptide increases mEPSC amplitude and frequency\". Experimental description: - Species of overexpressed AP2mu is not stated in the paper. Authors were contacted (dd 13/3/2018, haucke@fmp-berlin.de). Answer:\n\n\"Dear Pim,\nBoth were from rat (e.g. AP2mu was rat as were hippocampal neurons in culture).\nBest wishes,\nVolker\"\n\n- Authors refer to AP2mu siRNA \"AAGUGGAUGCCUUUCGGGUCA\" used in A. Motley et al., 2003 (PMID:12952941). Nucleotide BLAST matches AP2M1" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0593-3443" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" ;
        dc:date           "2022-08-13" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_BP_2859" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .

